# TEIL 1 — PRAKTISCHER MASCHINENBAU UND MASCHINENELEMENTE

Practical Machine Construction and Machine Elements

Folio Range: f.1r-A through f.95v-C

**○ f.1r**

DE: Datum 1.1.1493 / Konische Flamme und runder Wassertropfen / Zahnräder (1): Uhrengetriebe / Kraftübertragung

*IT: A dì primo di gienaro 1493 - Dating anchor. Zahnräder studies for clock mechanisms. Tempo = escapement (Hemmung). Discussion of force transmission via teeth vs. cords vs. contact.*

⚠ DATE: 1 January 1493 — Establishes codex timeline

⚠ Word lists NOT in mirror writing

⚠ Tempo = escapement (Hemmung) — technical terminology key

⚠ Carello/caregli = Ritzel (smaller gear) — terminology important for later folios

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 1)

**○ f.1v**

DE: Wörterliste mit Vorsilbe ass... / Eisentechnik: Brünieren und Ätzen

*IT: Word list with ass... prefix. Iron technique: browning and etching (biacca a olio = lead white as temporary coating).*

⚠ Word list NOT in mirror writing — educational self-instruction (Marinoni)

⚠ Brünierung = corrosion protection + decor

⚠ Bleiweiß technique: temporary coating for selective etching

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 1)

**○ f.2r**

DE: Wandlung von Rotation in alternierend lineare Bewegung durch Getriebe aus Zahnstangen und Zahnradsegmenten

*IT: Conversion of rotation into alternating linear motion. Two mechanisms: segmented gear with Drehlinge, and dual rack-and-pinion with rope.*

⚠ Central theme: rotation → alternating movement (appears ~30× in codex)

⚠ Drehling terminology critical (vs. Stockgetriebe)

⚠ Taddei: 'Durch Kurbelantrieb erzielte Wechselwirkung'

⚠ CORRELATION: Links to f.6v, 7v, 8v, 15r, 17r, 19v, 20r, 21r, 24r, 27r-31r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 1)

**○ f.2v**

DE: Wandlung: Kurbelwelle mit Zahnrad und Schnecke / Verteilung des Gewölbeschubs auf Pfeiler / Rollen mit schrägem Laufbrett

*IT: Conversion via crankshaft with gear and worm. Vault thrust distribution on pillars. Rollers with skewed plank or diagonal axis.*

⚠ Section A: Rotation → alternating (continuation from f.2r)

⚠ Section B: Vault statics — appears as insertion/afterthought

⚠ Section C: Roller mechanics — curro = transport roller

⚠ Subbio usage: rolling cylinder (later: Weberbaum, Walzwerk)

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 1)

**○ f.3r**

DE: Drehrichtung von Rädern im Getriebe / Zahnräder (2): Kraftübertragung

*IT: Direction of rotation in gear trains. Gear tooth force transmission with lever analysis.*

⚠ Odd/even counting rule for rotation direction

⚠ Ganzzahlig (integer) ratios for clocks vs. non-integer for mills

⚠ Miller practice: non-integer ratios reduce wear (gleichmäßiger Verschleiß)

⚠ DISCREPANCY: Maschat misread conclusion of Absatz 5 (mai potrà altro fare)

⚠ CORRELATION: Drehwirkungsänderung continues on f.5r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 1)

**○ f.4r**

DE: Uhr: Ausgleich nachlassender Federkraft

*IT: Clock: compensation of declining spring force. Spiral toothed rack with free-wheel mechanism as Drehmomentausgleich.*

⚠ MAESSTRA instrument (f.4v) — Leonardo's personal calibration device

⚠ Force vs. Weight distinction: Feder = Kraft, Gewicht wächst beim Fallen

⚠ Bedini/Reti: spiral mechanism 'not functioning' — DISPUTED by Klemm

⚠ Vite piramidata + corda = snail cam and chain (modern fusée equivalent)

⚠ CORRELATION: Similar mechanisms f.13v, 14r, 16r, 45r, 85r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 2)

**○ f.4v**

DE: Maesstra: Instrument zur Messung der Kraft eines Schraubengetriebes / Kraft von Blattfedern

*IT: MAESSTRA: 'Io ho creato a mme la maesstra, la quale fedelmente mi mostra i sua secreti' — Leonardo's self-designed experimental apparatus for measuring screw force. Spring mechanics.*

⚠ MAESSTRA = calibration instrument (congegno sperimentale per misurare l'attrito)

⚠ Verweis: '5° del nono' — internal cross-reference to lost theoretical treatise

⚠ Blattfeder studies: Leonardo refutes common beliefs about spring force

⚠ HOOKE'S LAW (1678): Leonardo's rejection NOT consistent with Ut tensio sic vis

⚠ Maschat notes missing text in 1974 German translation

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 2)

**○ f.5r**

DE: Zahnräder (3): Kraftübertragung und Berührungspunkte

*IT: Gear teeth contact points and force transmission. Leonardo establishes that contact must occur on the line connecting the two centers. Tooth wear and geometric analysis.*

⚠ Central contact line principle: -a-n- through -r-t-

⚠ Tooth thickness: 2/3 to 3/4 of spacing at mid-point

⚠ Friction quantified: 1/4 of load weight (Absatz 6)

⚠ Variable leverage during mesh affects force transmission

⚠ Fig. 12: Sägezähne 'assai durabili' — most durable tooth form

⚠ CORRELATION: Continues theory from f.1r, 3v; precedes f.5v studies

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 2)

**○ f.10r**

DE: Transmissionsketten (Gelenk- und Gliederketten) / Uhr: Schlagwerk-Steuerung / Wasserheber

*IT: Transmission chains (joint and link chains). Clock striking mechanism with spring release. Water lifting device.*

⚠ CHAIN TYPOLOGY: Strickleiterkette, Gelenkkette, Gliederkette, Schlingenkette

⚠ Absatz 2: 'cosa inposibile i' natura e pure è con effetto' — chains from single-piece links

⚠ Feldhaus: chain transmission wrongly attributed to Vaucanson (1770); Besson/Ramelli show earlier (1565/1588)

⚠ Philon of Byzantium chain-bucket (disputed until Nemisee finds)

⚠ SCHARNIERGELENKKETTE: Could function as Treib-, Förder-, or Lastkette (Maschat)

⚠ BICYCLE CONTROVERSY: Codex Atlanticus f.133v sketch — Marinoni/Pedretti vs. Lessing

⚠ CORRELATION: Chain studies continue f.10r; Freilauf mechanism on f.19v-21r uses similar principles

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.10v**

DE: Uhr: Planetenbeweger für astronomische Uhren

*IT: Clock mechanisms for astronomical displays: planet-movers, moon phase indicators. References Chiaravalle abbey clock.*

⚠ CHIARAVALLE CLOCK = primary dating anchor and technical model

⚠ Ptolemäischer Exzenter mechanism with pendulum weight (Fig. 3)

⚠ Mondphasen: Konzentrische Wellen for solar/lunar display (Fig. 4)

⚠ Siderischer Monat: ~27d 7h 43m vs. Synodischer Monat: ~29d 12h 44m

⚠ SIMONI CRITIQUE: Called Fig. 4 'completely wrong' — REFUTED by Hall/Bates

⚠ Globoidschnecke variations (Fig. 5-6) for phase rotation

⚠ CORRELATION: Chiaravalle references also f.11r, 11v; Codex Atlanticus f.1111v (399v)

⚠ WITNESS: System derives from Guglielmo della Volpaia (Florence contact)

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.11r**

DE: Uhr: Mondphasenzeiger nach Muster von Chiaravalle / Schlosstechnik: Drehhebel mit Federspannung

*IT: Moon phase indicator mechanisms (variants after Chiaravalle model). Lock technology: rotary lever with spring tension.*

⚠ MONDPHASEN variants: Schneckenkronrad (Fig. 1), Zahnrad-Ritzel (Fig. 2), Schnecke (Fig. 4)

⚠ 'poli in poli, come in Chiaravalle' — concentric axes like Chiaravalle clock

⚠ Winkelwelle mit Spiralmantel (Fig. 5) — angle shaft with spiral casing

⚠ FEDERSPANNUNG: 'Die Feder ist sicherer...nah bei den Achsen' — spring placement doctrine

⚠ CORRELATION: Chiaravalle mechanisms cross-ref f.10v; springs also f.9v, 49v, 50r, 66v, 79v

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.11v**

DE: Uhr: Uhrentechnische Elemente / Getriebeelemente

*IT: Clock elements: spindle with sprung pawls, crown wheel, switching cam drum. Gearing elements with half-toothed wheels.*

⚠ 'poli in poli, come in Chiaravalle' (Absatz 1) — DIRECT CITATION of abbey clock

⚠ Konzentrische Wellen: hour and minute hand transmission

⚠ Fig. 2: Kronrad + Spindel + Pendel — escapement sketch (function unclear)

⚠ Fig. 7: Zwei Übersetzungsstufen with direction reversal via half-toothing

⚠ Schrägverzahnung (Fig. 9): 'obbliqui, a uso di vite' — helical teeth like screw threads

⚠ CORRELATION: Escapement studies continue through codex; half-toothing critical for f.19v-21r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.12r**

DE: Balance der Kraft bei Hebeln und Seilzügen

*IT: Balance of force with levers and pulleys. Weight-counterweight equilibrium demonstrations.*

⚠ Isolierter Nachtrag zur Statik — inserted section on force balance

⚠ Influenced by Pseudo-Aristotelian Mechanica problemata (recently available in Italy)

⚠ 'Quanto magiore peso...meglio e più forte sarà sostenuto' — self-adjusting grip force

⚠ Similar demonstrations: Ms. Paris I f.132r, Codex Arundel f.40r, 79v, 282r

⚠ CORRELATION: Statics studies scattered throughout Part 2

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.12v**

DE: Lager: Antifriktionslager (Mehrfachscheiben, Pendelstützen)

*IT: Bearings: Anti-friction bearings (multiple discs, pendulum supports). Revolutionary ball bearing concepts.*

⚠ GIULIO WITNESS: 'Dice Giulio aver visto nella Magni[a]...' — German collaborator testimony

⚠ Giulio entered service: 18 March 1493 (dating evidence)

⚠ DOPPELSCHEIBENLAGER: Disc bearings reduce friction via übersetzung

⚠ PENDELSTÜTZENLAGER: Segment bearings for oscillating shafts (bells)

⚠ Gehärtet: 'tenperati' — hardened steel specification

⚠ RETI 1971: 'Leonardo introduced concept of friction ratio F/W'

⚠ Modern rediscovery: Leupold 1724 (Theatrum Machinarum)

⚠ CORRELATION: Bearing studies Part 2 f.88v-91v (103r-100r); ball bearings f.20v, 26r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.13r**

DE: Reibung: Abnutzung von Wellen, Achsen, Zähnen und Triebstöcken

*IT: Friction and wear: consumption of shafts, axles, teeth, and drive pins. Systematic wear analysis.*

⚠ Long vs. short shafts: load distribution affects wear

⚠ 'duro con duro' — hardened steel on hardened steel requirement

⚠ 10:1 wear ratio for 10:1 gear ratio (Absatz 7)

⚠ Triebstock wear: full-length vs. partial contact (Fig. 3-4)

⚠ Verschleiß vs. Reibung distinction (consumamento vs. confregazione)

⚠ CORRELATION: Wear studies also f.3r, 20r; Part 2 f.91v (100r)

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 3)

**○ f.13v**

DE: Zahnräder (6): Drehrichtung / Uhr: Schlagwerk-Steuerung / Uhr: Ausgleich nachlassender Federkraft / Kardanische Aufhängung

*IT: Gear rotation direction. Clock striking mechanism. Spring force compensation. Gimbal suspension for compass.*

⚠ PLANETARY-EPICYCLIC gear train (Fig. 2) — Moon analysis

⚠ Schlossscheibe: 12-notch striking control with progressive spacing

⚠ STACKFREED mechanism (Fig. 5) — spring brake with inclined plane

⚠ 'tenperata in circulo' — tempered steel ring spring

⚠ KARDANISCHE AUFHÄNGUNG: Gimbal for ship's compass (Fig. 6)

⚠ Villard de Honnecourt (1237), Kyeser, Fontana (~1440) precedents

⚠ Fontana: 'in urbe nostra Venetiarum...multe tales venduntur'

⚠ CORRELATION: Spring compensation f.4r, 14v, 16r, 45r; gimbals also Codex Atlanticus f.783r, 869r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.18v**

DE: Schraube: Globoidschneckenpaar / Ringförmige Schraubenfeder / Luntenschnappschloss

*IT: Double globoid worm drive. Ring-shaped spiral spring. Matchlock mechanism for scoppietto.*

⚠ GLOBOIDSCHNECKEN: Endlosschnecke via gleichsinnig rotating worms (Fig. 1)

⚠ 'vite sanza fine' — endless screw principle

⚠ Schraubrad vs. Schnecke: 11-gang short worm (Fig. 2)

⚠ LUNTENSCHLOSS: Complete flintlock specification ~115 years before le Bourgeoys

⚠ 'ufitio di quessto strumento è di dare foco allo sscoppietto'

⚠ Scoppietto: 2-3 piedi, 4-6 dramme lead ball (Madrid II f.98r table)

⚠ Automatic powder pan cover opening mechanism

⚠ CORRELATION: Globoid worms also f.19r; firearm studies throughout codex

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.19r**

DE: Uhr: Globoidschnecken-Getriebe / Oszillation durch Spannkraft

*IT: Globoid worm drives for torque compensation (clocks). Oscillation via tension.*

⚠ 'Vite perpetua...solo è da orilogi' (Fig. 1) — for clockwork only

⚠ Variable torque problem: force varies with distance from center

⚠ 4-tooth continuous engagement (Fig. 2) ensures 'continua equalità di forza'

⚠ Konische Spule compensation attempt (Fig. 1c) — INSUFFICIENT for torque fluctuation

⚠ Oscillation mechanisms (Fig. 3-4): flexible connections, twisted rope

⚠ CORRELATION: Globoid studies continue from f.18v; oscillation theory develops through Part 2

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.19v**

DE: Wandlung oszillierender in stete Rotation mittels Freilaufnabe (1)

*IT: Conversion of oscillating rotation into constant rotation using free-wheeling hub. MAJOR KINEMATIC DISCOVERY.*

⚠ FREE-WHEEL HUB: First known specification ~400 years before Fichtel & Sachs (1889)

⚠ Sperrklinke (pawl) + Sägezahnkranz (ratchet) convert sliding to rolling friction

⚠ 'osservino il principiato inpeto' — mechanism preserves initial impetus

⚠ Kugellager: Ball bearings on hub flange (Fig. 1d)

⚠ Vergüteter Stahl: Hardened steel for pawl and ratchet ring

⚠ IMPETUS DOCTRINE: Kinetic energy preservation principle

⚠ CORRELATION: f.20r provides mechanical details; f.21r discusses impetus theory

⚠ NO KNOWN PRECEDENTS: Francesco di Giorgio, Gruter show fixed triebstöcke

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.20r**

DE: Wandlung oszillierender in stete Rotation mittels Freilaufnabe (2) / Lager: Kugellager / Bohrer

*IT: Free-wheel hub (detailed mechanism). Ball bearing with globoid rollers. Gimlet drill.*

⚠ FREILAUF DETAILS: Drehling + Sägezahnkranz + Sperrklinke + Feder

⚠ 'si volta per un sol verso...unita col suo polo...per l'altro...libera'

⚠ KUGELLAGER: Holzkugeln between globoid rollers on axes (Fig. 1)

⚠ Käfig principle: Globoid rollers prevent ball-to-ball contact

⚠ Reti 1971: Ball-race ring 'reinvented 1772'

⚠ Zahnrad wear: 10× faster for 10:1 ratio (Absatz 3)

⚠ CORRELATION: Ball bearings also f.26r; drill ref f.23v, 24v, Part 2 f.72r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.21r**

DE: Wandlung oszillierender in stete Rotation mittels Freilaufnabe (3) / Impetus rotierender Mühlsteine

*IT: Free-wheel hub (kinematic energy analysis). Impetus of rotating millstones — THEORETICAL FOUNDATION.*

⚠ IMPETUS THEORY: 'Io ho inparato dai bocalari...' — potters' wheel observation

⚠ Resonant accumulation: One water source could drive TWO mills via impetus

⚠ Segmented gears: 1/8 or 1/6 circle reduces momentum reversal load

⚠ 'manco fuga' principle: Less 'flight' (inertia) = easier direction change

⚠ MILLSTONE ACCELERATION (Absatz 4): Progressive speed increase via repeated impulse

⚠ Part 2 f.60v: 'Impetus è accrescimento di velocità nel moto'

⚠ Albert von Sachsen, Nikolaus Oresme precedents (Duhem, Wolff)

⚠ CORRELATION: Impetus discussed Part 2; Clagett 1973 catalogues other instances

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.21v**

DE: Mehlschüttelwerk / Schlagbaum oder Leiter mit Kurbel

*IT: Flour shaker of grain mill. Turnpike barrier or ladder with crank mechanism.*

⚠ BEUTELWERK: Sieving mechanism for flour/bran separation

⚠ Previously attributed to Turriano (1565) or Ramelli (1588)

⚠ Zwickauer Chronik 1502 = oldest German text reference

⚠ Leonardo dates invention to 15th century — EARLIEST KNOWN

⚠ Schlagbaum/Leiter: Crank-driven lifting bar with counterweight

⚠ Schnecke + Stirnrad mechanism for mechanical advantage

⚠ CORRELATION: Similar in Codex Forster I.2 f.46v, Trivulziano f.29r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

**○ f.22r**

DE: Hebezangen für große Steine

*IT: Lifting claws for large stones. Wolf and tongs mechanisms.*

⚠ ERNST 1973: Leonardo first to formulate self-tightening grip law

⚠ 'Quanto magiore peso...meglio e più forte sarà sostenuto'

⚠ Zangenlöcher: Side-cut grip holes (12th c. evidence)

⚠ Wolf: Keilwirkung or Spreizwirkung via top hole (11th c. evidence)

⚠ Villard de Honnecourt first to draw wolf mechanism

⚠ Aachen Minster: 2m tongs, ~70kg (ca. 1930 in Kreuzgang)

⚠ CORRELATION: Codex Atlanticus f.38r, 1001r; Schleppzange f.84r

STATUS: ANALYZED (Batch 4)

